46. Antonio Gramsci, Further Selections from the Prison Notebooks, edited and translated by Derek Boothman (Minneapolis: University of Minnesota Press, 1995), pp. 315-18. Gramsci does not note the sexism of such an attitude, but for today’s reader the power of his critique rests on this notion, making one wonder at the appropriateness of his comparison.

47. Perry Anderson, ‘The Antinomies of Antonio Gramsci’，New Left Review 100 (November 1976-January 1977), pp. 5-79; Robert Bocock, Hegemony (Chichester: Ellis Horwood, 1986); and Hoare and Nowell Smith, in SPN, p. 207.

