11. Derrida essentially redefines ‘writing’ to be much broader than ‘phonetic writing’ and to include any form of coding or inscription. Jacques Derrida, Of Grammatology, translated by Gayatri Chakrovorty Spivak (Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press, 1974), pp. 101-40.

12. Derrida, Of Grammatology, especially pp. 1-94.

